subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] QuickScript manual
msgSnippet: Dear Frank: I have been on vacation recently and fell behind in attending to e-mail.  I just read your post regarding your search for a copy of the Quikscript
messageBody:
Dear Frank:

I have been on vacation recently and fell behind in attending to e-mail.  I just read your post regarding your search for a copy of the Quikscript manual.

I would like to get the manual online, but I do not have time to do this now.  Unfortunately, I do not know any other source online for the manual at this time.  I have a copy of the manual and would be willing to copy it for you.  Send me $2.00 to defray copying and mailing costs along with your address, and I will get a copy to you. 

Thanks for your interest.

Paige Gabhart

At 01:59 AM 4/20/2001 +0000, you wrote:
Hello--
Am very excited to have discovered this site just today. I've been a
so-so reader of Shavian (as in Androcles and the Lion) for many
years, but am most eager to obtain a copy of Read's QuickScript
Manual. Can anyone please inform me as to how or where I may obtain a
copy. Is it downloadable from anywhere? Or available as a book(let)
to order? Your assistance will be sincerely appreciated.
---Frank
